FuelTrack LK — Project Overview
=================================

1. Introduction
---------------
FuelTrack LK is a smart fuel station finder and queue tracking mobile application
designed for drivers in Sri Lanka. During fuel shortages and high-demand periods,
drivers waste hours in queues without knowing which station has fuel, how long the
queue is, or when the best time to visit would be. FuelTrack LK solves this by
providing real-time fuel availability, community-reported queue conditions, and
AI-powered predictions — all in a single mobile app.

This is a university group project developed by W.D.C.S. Gunathunga
(Sandeepa Gunathunga), targeting the Western Province of Sri Lanka.


2. Problem Statement
---------------------
Sri Lankan drivers face these daily problems:

  - No way to know which nearby station has the fuel type they need
  - No visibility into queue length before physically driving to a station
  - Wasted time and fuel driving to stations that are closed or out of stock
  - No historical data to predict when queues will be shorter
  - No community platform to share real-time station conditions
  - No personal tracking of fuel expenses and consumption patterns


3. Solution
-----------
FuelTrack LK addresses every problem above:

  REAL-TIME AVAILABILITY     → Live fuel stock status for each station and fuel type
  QUEUE VISIBILITY           → Community-reported queue lengths with wait time estimates
  SMART DISCOVERY            → Search and filter stations by fuel type, queue, distance
  AI PREDICTIONS             → Machine learning-based busy hour forecasts
  COMMUNITY REPORTING        → Anonymous queue and availability reports from drivers
  EXPENSE TRACKING           → Personal fuel purchase records and spending analytics
  PUSH NOTIFICATIONS         → Alerts for fuel arrivals, queue changes, and price updates


4. Target Audience
------------------
  Primary:   Vehicle owners and drivers in Sri Lanka's Western Province
             (Colombo, Kotte, Rajagiriya, Nugegoda, Battaramulla)
  Secondary: Fleet managers, delivery service operators, fuel station owners
  Scale:     Designed to expand nationwide across all provinces


5. Technology Stack
-------------------

  FRONTEND
    Framework:       React Native (Expo SDK 57)
    Language:        JavaScript (ES6+)
    React Version:   React 19
    Runtime:         React Native 0.86
    Navigation:      React Navigation 7 (native-stack + bottom-tabs)
    Icons:           @expo/vector-icons (MaterialIcons, FontAwesome)
    UI Libraries:    expo-linear-gradient, react-native-svg, react-native-gesture-handler
    Testing Device:  Expo Go (over LAN)

  BACKEND
    Database:        Firebase Realtime Database
    Authentication:  Firebase Authentication (Email/Password + Social Login)
    Notifications:   Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)
    Storage:         Firebase Storage (for station images — future)

  TOOLS & INFRASTRUCTURE
    Version Control: GitHub
    API Testing:     Postman (as needed)
    Package Manager: npm


6. Team Responsibilities
------------------------

  Member 1 — Frontend, UI/UX & Maps
    - React Native screens and components
    - Navigation flow and tab bar design
    - Search, filter, and display logic
    - Map integration for station locations
    - Responsive layouts and animations

  Member 2 — Backend, Database & Firebase
    - Firebase Authentication setup
    - Firebase Realtime Database structure design
    - CRUD operations for all collections
    - Fuel availability update logic
    - Queue reports storage and retrieval
    - Fuel price storage and history
    - User expense records management
    - Push notification system (FCM)
    - Admin functions and user management


7. Functional Requirements
--------------------------

  FR-01   User registration with email verification
  FR-02   Secure login (email/password)
  FR-03   Social login (Google, Facebook)
  FR-04   Real-time fuel availability updates per station
  FR-05   Queue reporting by community users
  FR-06   Queue monitoring with vehicle count and wait time
  FR-07   Estimated waiting time calculation and storage
  FR-08   Fuel price tracking with current and historical data
  FR-09   Fuel consumption analytics per user
  FR-10   Monthly fuel usage tracking
  FR-11   Weekly spending analytics and summaries
  FR-12   Station facility information management
  FR-13   Push notifications for fuel alerts and supply arrivals
  FR-14   Community-based reporting with anonymous submissions
  FR-15   Fuel station management (admin)
  FR-16   System administration and user management
  FR-17   Nearby station discovery with distance calculation
  FR-18   Search stations by name and address
  FR-19   Filter stations by fuel type, queue status, and availability
  FR-20   AI-powered busy hour predictions
  FR-21   Saved locations (home, work, custom addresses)
  FR-22   User profile management (name, email, vehicle info)
  FR-23   Notification preferences and settings


8. Non-Functional Requirements
-------------------------------

  NFR-01  Secure authentication with encrypted credentials
  NFR-02  Reliable real-time data synchronization (< 2 second latency)
  NFR-03  Fast read/write operations on Firebase Realtime Database
  NFR-04  Scalable database structure supporting thousands of users
  NFR-05  Efficient push notification delivery
  NFR-06  Offline-capable with local data caching
  NFR-07  Cross-platform compatibility (Android and iOS via React Native)
  NFR-08  Responsive UI that works on all screen sizes
  NFR-09  Battery-efficient background operations
  NFR-10  GDPR-compliant data handling for user information


